sed on the single events outside the energy range of [3.5, 4.1] MeV , in which the dominant background is from the natural radioactivity and muon-induced unstable isotopes, which are summarized in Fig. 2 and more details can be found in Abusleme et al. (2021a). In the model independent approach of the ES measurement, the ${ }^{8} \\mathrm{~B}$ neutrino flux and two oscillation parameters $\\sin ^{2} \\theta_{12}$ and $\\Delta m_{21}^{2}$ are simultaneously"
