ype least squares function, denoted as $\\chi^{2}$, is defined as follows,\n\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\chi^{2}= & \\chi_{\\text {stat }}^{2}(\\mathrm{CC})+\\chi_{\\text {stat }}^{2}(\\mathrm{NC})+\\chi_{\\text {stat }}^{2}(\\mathrm{ES})+\\chi_{\\text {syst }}^{2} \\\\\n= & 2 \\times \\sum_{i=1}^{10}\\left[\\sum_{j_{\\mathrm{C}}=1}^{90}\\left(N_{\\mathrm{pre}}^{\\mathrm{C}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{C}}}\\right)-N_{\\mathrm{obs}}^{\\mathrm{C}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{C}}}\\right)+N_{\\mathrm{obs}}^{\\mathrm{C}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{C}}}\\right) \\cdot \\log \\frac{N_{\\mathrm{obs}}^{\\mathrm{C}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{C}}}\\right)}{N_{\\mathrm{pre}}^{\\mathrm{C}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{C}}}\\right)}\\right)\\right. \\\\\n& \\left.+\\sum_{j_{\\mathrm{S}}=1}^{140}\\left(N_{\\mathrm{pre}}^{\\mathrm{S}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{S}}}\\right)-N_{\\mathrm{obs}}^{\\mathrm{S}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{S}}}\\right)+N_{\\mathrm{obs}}^{\\mathrm{S}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{S}}}\\right) \\cdot \\log \\frac{N_{\\mathrm{obs}}^{\\mathrm{S}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{S}}}\\right)}{N_{\\mathrm{pre}}^{\\mathrm{S}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{S}}}\\right)}\\right)\\right]\\right. \\\\\n& +\\left(\\frac{\\varepsilon_{\\mathrm{A}}^{\\mathrm{ES}}}{\\sigma_{\\mathrm{X}}^{\\mathrm{ES}}}\\right)^{2}+\\left(\\frac{\\varepsilon_{\\mathrm{A}}^{\\mathrm{NC}}}{\\sigma_{\\mathrm{X}}^{\\mathrm{NC}}}\\right)^{2}+\\left(\\frac{\\varepsilon_{\\mathrm{A}}^{\\mathrm{CC}}}{\\sigma_{\\mathrm{X}}^{\\mathrm{CC}}}\\right)^{2}+\\sum_{k_{\\mathrm{C}}}\\left(\\frac{\\varepsilon_{\\mathrm{B}}^{k_{\\mathrm{C}}}}{\\sigma_{\\mathrm{B}}^{k_{\\mathrm{C}}}}\\right)^{2}+\\sum_{k_{\\mathrm{S}}}\\left(\\frac{\\varepsilon_{\\mathrm{B}}^{k_{\\mathrm{S}}}}{\\sigma_{\\mathrm{B}}^{k_{\\mathrm{S}}}}\\right)^{2} \\\\\n& +\\left(\\frac{\\varepsilon_{\\mathrm{eff}}^{\\mathrm{C}}}{\\sigma_{\\mathrm{eff}}^{\\mathrm{C}}}\\right)^{2}+\\left(\\frac{\\varepsilon_{\\mathrm{eff}}^{\\mathrm{S}}}{\\sigma_{\\mathrm{eff}}^{\\mathrm{S}}}\\right)^{2}+\\left(\\varepsilon_{\\mathrm{s}}\\right)^{2}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n\nwhere $\\chi_{\\text {stat }}^{2}(\\mathrm{CC}), \\chi_{\\text {stat }}^{2}(\\mathrm{NC})$, and $\\chi_{\\text {stat }}^{2}(\\mathrm{ES})$ are statistical parts of the CC, NC and ES channels in the $\\chi^{2}$ function, respectively. These components are presented in the second and third rows of Eq. (5). The index $j_{\\mathrm{C}}$ ranges from 1 to 90 for the CC measurement, representing the energy range from 5 MeV to 14 MeV with an equal bin width of 0.1 MeV . For the NC measurement, $j_{\\mathrm{S}}$ ranges from 16 to 21 , while for the ES measurement, $j_{\\mathrm{S}}$ spans from 1 to 15 and from 22 to 140 covering the energy range from 2 MeV to 16 MeV with an equal bin width of 0.1 MeV . The predicted numbers of signal and background events, $N_{\\mathrm{pre}}^{\\mathrm{C}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{C}}}\\right)$ and $N_{\\mathrm{pre}}^{\\mathrm{S}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{S}}}\\right)$ are calculated for the $i$-th zenith angle bin and the $j_{\\mathrm{C}}$-th or $j_{\\mathrm{S}}$-th visible energy bin of the correlated and single event samples, respectively\n\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& N_{\\mathrm{pre}}^{\\mathrm{C}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{C}}}\\right)=\\left(1+\\varepsilon_{\\mathrm{eff}}^{\\mathrm{C}}\\right) S_{\\mathrm{pre}}^{\\mathrm{CC}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{C}}}\\right)+\\sum_{k_{\\mathrm{C}}}\\left(1+\\varepsilon_{\\mathrm{B}}^{k_{\\mathrm{C}}}\\right) D_{\\mathrm{pre}}^{k_{\\mathrm{C}}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{C}}}\\right) \\\\\n& N_{\\mathrm{pre}}^{\\mathrm{S}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{S}}}\\right)=\\left(1+\\varepsilon_{\\mathrm{eff}}^{\\mathrm{S}}\\right)\\left[S_{\\mathrm{pre}}^{\\mathrm{NC}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{C}}}\\right)+S_{\\mathrm{pre}}^{\\mathrm{ES}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{C}}}\\right)\\right]+\\sum_{k_{\\mathrm{S}}}\\left(1+\\varepsilon_{\\mathrm{B}}^{k_{\\mathrm{S}}}\\right) D_{\\mathrm{pre}}^{k_{\\mathrm{S}}}\\left(\\theta_{z}^{i}, E_{\\mathrm{vis}}^{j_{\\mathrm{S}}}\\right)\n\\end{aligned}\n$$"
